My Own Examples (3)

  • I blend the my selfie into the Mona Lisa image.
  • I do both poisson blending and the mixed gradient blending and then compare the results.
  • The detailed algorithm is explained on the "AI621_20225421_penguin" and "AI621_20225421_toy" file.

Load Image

im_background = imresize(im2double(imread('./data/custom/monalisa.jpeg')),0.4,'bilinear');
im_object1 = imresize(im2double(imread('./data/custom/selfie.jpeg')), 0.5, 'bilinear');
im_background2 = imresize(im2double(imread('./data/custom/girl_pearl.jpeg')),0.4,'bilinear');

Get mask from the source image and align with the target image

  • I downsize the source face about 0.8 times for realisting compositing
obj1_mask = getMask(im_object1);
Draw polygon around source object in clockwise order, q to stop
[im_s1, mask_s1] = alignSource(im_object1, obj1_mask, im_background,0.8);
choose target bottom-center location

Poisson Blending

im_blend = poissonBlend(im_s1, mask_s1, im_background);
figure(3), hold off, imshow(im_blend);
imwrite(im_blend,'custom3.png')

Mixed-Gradient Blending

im_blend_mix = mixedBlend(im_s1, mask_s1, im_background);
figure(3), hold off, imshow(im_blend_mix);
imwrite(im_blend_mix,'custom3_mix.png')
  • The above two images are the results of poisson blending and the mixed gradient blending.
  • Looking at the case of poisson blending, although it does not blend perfectly, it blends well with the target's pixel values as the gradient of the source is well observed. The imperfect part seems to be the limit of the masked image.
  • In the case of the mixed-gradient method, the same problem as in example2 occurred. The gradient of the target background (Mona Lisa's eyes, nose, and mouth) is larger than the gradient of the source image, so the target image is reflected as it is. This is also a problem caused by the failure of the target image's objects(eyes, nose, and mouth) to be completely aligned with the source image's objects.
  • Considering these points comprehensively, poisson blending makes better blending result.
function [output] = poissonBlend(im_s,mask_s,im_background)
[imh, imw, nn] = size(im_background);
im2var = zeros(imh, imw);
im2var(1:imh*imw) = 1:imh*imw;
% mask_1 x,y -> A ncol
[y,x] = find(mask_s ~= 0);
[y_s,x_s] = find(mask_s == 0);
% matrix A
nrow = imh*imw;
ncol = size(x,1)+size(x_s,1);
A = sparse([], [], [], ncol, nrow, 0);
b = sparse(ncol,1);
output = zeros(imh,imw,nn);
for c = 1:nn
t = im_background(:,:,c);
s = im_s(:,:,c);
e = 0;
 
% source gradient .
% , boundary , target_j source_i
for i = 1:size(x,1)
e = e+1;
right_term = 0;
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i))) = 4;
if mask_s(y(i),x(i)-1) == 0
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i)-1)) = 0;
right_term = right_term + s(y(i),x(i)) - s(y(i),x(i)-1) + t(y(i),x(i)-1);
else
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i)-1)) = -1;
right_term = right_term + s(y(i),x(i)) - s(y(i),x(i)-1);
end
 
if mask_s(y(i),x(i)+1) == 0
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i)+1)) = 0;
right_term = right_term + s(y(i),x(i)) - s(y(i),x(i)+1) + t(y(i),x(i)+1);
else
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i)+1)) = -1;
right_term = right_term + s(y(i),x(i)) - s(y(i),x(i)+1);
end
if mask_s(y(i)-1,x(i)) == 0
A(e, im2var(y(i)-1,x(i))) = 0;
right_term = right_term + s(y(i),x(i)) - s(y(i)-1,x(i)) + t(y(i)-1,x(i));
else
A(e, im2var(y(i)-1,x(i))) = -1;
right_term = right_term + s(y(i),x(i)) - s(y(i)-1,x(i));
end
 
if mask_s(y(i)+1,x(i)) == 0
A(e, im2var(y(i)+1,x(i))) = 0;
right_term = right_term + s(y(i),x(i)) - s(y(i)+1,x(i)) + t(y(i)+1,x(i));
else
A(e, im2var(y(i)+1,x(i))) = -1;
right_term = right_term + s(y(i),x(i)) - s(y(i)+1,x(i));
end
 
b(e) = right_term;
end
% target pixel
for i = 1:size(x_s,1)
e = e+1;
A(e,im2var(y_s(i),x_s(i))) = 1;
b(e) = t(y_s(i),x_s(i));
end
v = A\b;
n=0;
for j = 1:imw
for i = 1:imh
n = n+1;
output(i,j,c) = v(n);
end
end
end
end
 
function [output] = mixedBlend(im_s, mask_s, im_bg)
[imh, imw, nn] = size(im_bg);
im2var = zeros(imh, imw);
im2var(1:imh*imw) = 1:imh*imw;
% mask_1 x,y -> A ncol
[y,x] = find(mask_s ~= 0);
[y_s,x_s] = find(mask_s == 0);
% matrix A
nrow = imh*imw;
ncol = size(x,1) + size(x_s,1);
A = sparse([], [], [], ncol, nrow, 0);
b = sparse(ncol,1);
output = zeros(imh,imw,nn);
for c = 1:nn
t = im_bg(:,:,c);
s = im_s(:,:,c);
e = 0;
for i = 1:size(x,1)
e = e+1;
 
right_term = 0;
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i))) = 4;
 
if mask_s(y(i),x(i)-1) == 0
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i)-1)) = 0;
right_term = right_term + mix_compare(y(i),x(i),t,s,0,-1) + t(y(i),x(i)-1);
else
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i)-1)) = -1;
right_term = right_term + mix_compare(y(i),x(i),t,s,0,-1);
end
 
if mask_s(y(i),x(i)+1) == 0
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i)+1)) = 0;
right_term = right_term + mix_compare(y(i),x(i),t,s,0,1) + t(y(i),x(i)+1);
else
A(e, im2var(y(i),x(i)+1)) = -1;
right_term = right_term + mix_compare(y(i),x(i),t,s,0,1);
end
if mask_s(y(i)-1,x(i)) == 0
A(e, im2var(y(i)-1,x(i))) = 0;
right_term = right_term + mix_compare(y(i),x(i),t,s,-1,0) + t(y(i)-1,x(i));
else
A(e, im2var(y(i)-1,x(i))) = -1;
right_term = right_term + mix_compare(y(i),x(i),t,s,-1,0);
end
 
if mask_s(y(i)+1,x(i)) == 0
A(e, im2var(y(i)+1,x(i))) = 0;
right_term = right_term + mix_compare(y(i),x(i),t,s,1,0) + t(y(i)+1,x(i));
else
A(e, im2var(y(i)+1,x(i))) = -1;
right_term = right_term + mix_compare(y(i),x(i),t,s,1,0);
end
 
b(e) = right_term;
end
for i = 1:size(x_s,1)
e = e+1;
A(e,im2var(y_s(i),x_s(i))) = 1;
b(e) = t(y_s(i),x_s(i));
end
v = A\b;
n=0;
for j = 1:imw
for i = 1:imh
n = n+1;
output(i,j,c) = v(n);
end
end
end
end
 
function [d] = mix_compare(y,x,t,s,a,b)
 
if abs(t(y,x)-t(y+a,x+b)) < abs(s(y,x)-s(y+a,x+b))
d = s(y,x)-s(y+a,x+b);
else
d = t(y,x)-t(y+a,x+b);
end
end
 
function [mask, poly] = getMask(im)
% [mask, poly] = getMask(im)
% Asks user to draw polygon around input image. Provides binary mask of
% polygon and a chain of all interior boundary points.
 
disp('Draw polygon around source object in clockwise order, q to stop')
figure(1), hold off, imagesc(im), axis image;
sx = [];
sy = [];
while 1
figure(1)
[x, y, b] = ginput(1);
if b=='q'
break;
end
sx(end+1) = x;
sy(end+1) = y;
hold on, plot(sx, sy, '*-');
end
 
mask = poly2mask(sx, sy, size(im, 1), size(im, 2));
if nargout>1
[poly.x, poly.y] = mask2chain(mask);
end
end
 
function [im_s2, mask2] = alignSource(im_s, mask, im_t,a)
% im_s2 = alignSource(im_s, mask, im_t)
% Asks user for bottom-center position and outputs an aligned source image.
 
figure(1), hold off, imagesc(im_s), axis image
figure(2), hold off, imagesc(im_t), axis image
[y, x] = find(mask);
y1 = min(y)-1; y2 = max(y)+1; x1 = min(x)-1; x2 = max(x)+1;
im_s2 = zeros(size(im_t));
disp('choose target bottom-center location')
[tx, ty] = ginput(1);
 
yind = (y1:y2);
yind2 = (yind -max(y))*a + round(ty);
yind2 = round(yind2);
xind = (x1:x2);
xind2 = (xind - round(mean(x)))*a + round(tx);
xind2 = round(xind2);
 
y = (y - max(y))*a + round(ty);
x = (x - round(mean(x)))*a + round(tx);
x = round(x);
y = round(y);
ind = y + (x-1)*size(im_t, 1) ;
mask2 = false(size(im_t, 1), size(im_t, 2));
mask2(ind) = true;
im_s2(yind2, xind2, :) = im_s(yind, xind, :);
im_t(repmat(mask2, [1 1 3])) = im_s2(repmat(mask2, [1 1 3]));
 
figure(1), hold off, imagesc(im_s2), axis image;
figure(2), hold off, imagesc(im_t), axis image;
drawnow;
end
